Remarks. Due to the fact that
E. oplophoroides
is mainly collected as by-catch in artisanal shrimp fishing, many studies have been carried out on this species along the São Paulo coast, such as population and reproductive aspects (
Fransozo et al. 2005
;
Braga et al. 2009
;
Baeza et al. 2010
;
Nunes et al. 2010
) and larval morphology (Negreiros- Fransozo et al. 2002). Sequences accession number (GenBank): CCDB 3769 - 16S ( KU312980 ), COI ( KU313009 ).
